menu "breadboard: bb_ota_push"

config BB_OTA_PUSH_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register OTA push HTTP route via bb_registry"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_ota_push self-registers its HTTP route handler
        through bb_registry. Disable this if you want to keep bb_ota_push's
        public C API but drive route registration manually or skip the route
        entirely (e.g. headless OTA-driver use).

config BB_OTA_PUSH_WDT_EXTENDED_S
    int "Task WDT timeout (s) during OTA push receive+write phase"
    range 30 1800
    default 300
    help
        Same rationale as CONFIG_BB_OTA_PULL_WDT_EXTENDED_S: esp_ota_write
        triggers cache_disable, and the consumer pause callback may hold
        the mining task in a semaphore wait for the full upload window.
        WDT-subscribed tasks (idle, mining) cannot reset the WDT during
        these windows; bb_ota_push temporarily reconfigures the WDT timeout
        for the duration of the push and restores
        CONFIG_ESP_TASK_WDT_TIMEOUT_S on exit.

endmenu
